[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering H2 database behavior**\n\nI’m evaluating how Hibernate’s connection provider might open or close connections as needed. With the H2 in-memory database, it exists only while there's an open connection. After a commit, if the connection closes before a database snapshot is taken, the schema could vanish! But it seems that if I use H2 with no DB_CLOSE_DELAY set, it will persist as long as the connection remains open. That’s an interesting aspect to note!\n\n**Considering database connections**\n\nI’m thinking about the connection release after transactions. When no connection remains, the schema drops, and current tests use \"jdbc:h2:mem:test,\" likely maintaining connections in the entity manager. Upon commit, the connection might get released, potentially causing issues if tables are missing due to all connections closing. \n\nTo avoid errors, using `DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1` with unique database names per test, maybe by utilizing UUIDs, could be ideal. I’ll check if hyphens in the H2 DB name work too, but keeping it straightforward with `Long.toHexString(System.nanoTime())` seems like a solid plan!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_08f152761ff670690169eff2b07160819f8c7d8df4fa294c28\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp7_K9k4vAJ9JAHmZ4lRMdinh_xE5NfAiU1fisOLJB2ZNOVPYFeE0_KFqZTNpDRCXQili3RR_K9Pr5eiS8TJ36kCI_4IJe813f0MCVdmiau0gR28bOXGE5kJzKHUWORAt3f8F7nbc0nwmvEuMGoNfARKdp89cgE9LvY8N5o97WkKnYPb4LxcCm7eztslnNjAm0rej7AUXLRFsiPRcIVyqjL1Tvk603GSVk_-uiuA-HFw-3893vDzIBAREJM-l0AU84yV-aEcVOYOEy1u5rSoQZIVfTIdyYFM3R3lGrmD66tpLxxezB31hvJmKF_Yk2cQ7nOZrxo9R_U1QWYSshzHkNBSRMZXD9fAdGZTC927e8YlzIeiVM561PsfjUxjANfmLLimmvbztWgC78C60KgdRoYTB12e6uwVrEIRa4T2LQt9Su4LJpzmjlaXVgzrSqQw1awiJL5E3q49Ia65oHJzTPI_qeVWGugO8ERULlITAI9HfdjSzKZPbqsUeSeUOeDf2GlNHv2wPbbQVb0gUu9BkolMtSYzHP_HUoUSCUmpDNkM-doDiEEZKPPgMLR27W2HQraP_S0Yt631OA0tbkg1MxOoMeTezibzF5TNaiOd8UfNvGsm